What should you do if a member of your household gets COVID-19?
Photo: Richard Drury/Getty Images Photo: Richard Drury/Getty Images Image 1 of / 33 Caption Close What should you do if a member of your household gets COVID-19?
Creating a safe situation in a household with one or multiple infected patients is tricky, so it's helpful to plan ahead and prepare for sickness.
"But if the household members are all staying far apart and not coming into one another’s spaces, masks aren’t as important.
Check in with your doctor about how long to keep household members and these extreme measures in place.